---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import Terminal from "../../components/Terminal.astro";
import CodeEditor from "../../components/CodeEditor.astro";
import { getFeaturesNav } from "../../data/nav";
import GetStartedCTA from "../../components/GetStartedCTA.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const current = `${base}features/readiness/`;
const nav = getFeaturesNav(base);
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Readiness Checks - fuku"
  description="HTTP, TCP, and log-based health checks for services."
  current={current}
  nav={nav}
  section="features"
  breadcrumb={[{ label: "Features", href: `${base}features/` }, { label: "Readiness Checks", href: current }]}
>
  <span class="kicker">// features &middot; readiness</span>
  <h1>Readiness Checks</h1>
  <p class="lead">A started process is not a healthy service. fuku polls until your service actually accepts requests.</p>

  <div class="section-eyebrow">How it works</div>
  <h2>Poll until healthy.</h2>

  <p>
    When a service has a readiness check configured, fuku waits for it to pass before marking the service as ready. The next tier only begins after all services in the current tier are ready.
  </p>

  <Terminal title="fuku run default">
    <pre><span class="dim">│</span> <span class="purple bold">tier foundation</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>   <span class="yellow">&#9675;</span> auth        <span class="yellow">checking</span> <span class="dim">http localhost:8081/health...</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>   <span class="yellow">&#9675;</span> gateway     <span class="yellow">checking</span> <span class="dim">http localhost:8082/health...</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>   <span class="green">&#10003;</span> gateway     <span class="muted">ready</span>    <span class="dim">1.8s</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>   <span class="green">&#10003;</span> auth        <span class="muted">ready</span>    <span class="dim">2.1s</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>
<span class="dim">│</span> <span class="purple bold">tier platform</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>   <span class="yellow">&#9675;</span> api         <span class="yellow">checking</span> <span class="dim">http localhost:8080/health...</span>
<span class="dim">│</span>   <span class="green">&#10003;</span> api         <span class="muted">ready</span>    <span class="dim">4.5s</span>
</pre>
  </Terminal>

  <div class="section-eyebrow">Three check types</div>
  <h2>Pick the one that matches your service.</h2>

  <h3>HTTP</h3>

  <p>Wait for an HTTP endpoint to respond with a 2xx status code:</p>

  <CodeEditor title="fuku.yaml" lang="yaml" code={`services:
  api:
    dir: ./api
    readiness:
      type: http
      url: http://localhost:8080/health
      timeout: 30s
      interval: 1s`} />

  <h3>TCP</h3>

  <p>Wait for a TCP port to accept connections:</p>

  <CodeEditor title="fuku.yaml" lang="yaml" code={`services:
  gateway:
    dir: ./gateway
    readiness:
      type: tcp
      address: localhost:9000
      timeout: 10s
      interval: 1s`} />

  <h3>Log</h3>

  <p>Wait for a specific pattern to appear in the service's output:</p>

  <CodeEditor title="fuku.yaml" lang="yaml" code={`services:
  grpc-server:
    dir: ./grpc
    readiness:
      type: log
      pattern: "gRPC server started"
      timeout: 30s`} />

  <div class="section-eyebrow">Configuration</div>
  <h2>Per-service, in fuku.yaml.</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Field</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>type</code></td>
        <td><code>http</code>, <code>tcp</code>, or <code>log</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>url</code></td>
        <td>HTTP endpoint to check (http type only)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>address</code></td>
        <td>Host:port to connect to (tcp type only)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>pattern</code></td>
        <td>String to match in log output (log type only)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>timeout</code></td>
        <td>Maximum time to wait before marking as failed</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>interval</code></td>
        <td>Time between check attempts (http/tcp only)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="section-eyebrow">Retries</div>
  <h2>Automatic retry on failure.</h2>

  <p>If a readiness check times out, fuku can retry the service start based on your retry configuration:</p>

  <CodeEditor title="fuku.yaml" lang="yaml" code={`retry:
  attempts: 3                   # Max retry attempts (default: 3)
  backoff: 500ms                # Initial backoff duration (default: 500ms)`} />

  <GetStartedCTA />
</DocsLayout>
